JSON Web Token - self contained way to securely transmit data and information between two parties using a JSON object.

JWT can be digitally signed, which in return allows server to knof if JWT has been changed at all.

Three seperate parts by dots
aaa.bbb.ccc

Header.Payload.Signature

JWT Header consist two parts:
alg - the algorithm for signing
typ - specific type of token

{"alg":"HS256, "typ":"JWT"}

JWT Payload data contains claims
- there are three different types of claims
1. Registered (Predefined, recommended but not mandatory)
- be sure that there is expiration date
2. Public 
3. Private

{
    "sub":"1234567890",  // sub - subject, ID of token
    "name":"Eric Ruby",
    "given_name":"Eric",
    "family_name":"Roby",
    "email":"codingwithroby@gmail.com",
    "admin":true
}

JWT Signature - algorithm in the header to hash out the encoded header. Saved on the server that the client does not have access to.

HMACSHA256(
    base64UrlEncode(header) + "." +
    base64UrlEncode(payload), 
    secret
)

